is exposed in the matrix, an hsp70 molecule binds to it, preventing further backsliding and thereby making the movement directional. Thus, a hand-over-hand binding of multiple hsp70 proteins translocates the polypeptide chain into the matrix.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p><a href=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/ucw9U.png\" rel=\"nofollow\"><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/ucw9U.png\" alt=\"Image- thermal ratchet\"><\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>What does thermal motion mean here? I will be obliged if somebody could explain it.<\/p>\n","question_id":44864,"tags":["mitochondria"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":13,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-on6yuwN5JEs/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAAABU/8oD_p798mqw/photo.jpg?sz=128","user_type":"registered","user_id":16460,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/16460/sanjukta-ghosh","reputation":432,"display_name":"Sanjukta Ghosh","accept_rate":38},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1sIMq.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4108,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4108/remi-b","reputation":22909,"display_name":"Remi.b","accept_rate":88},"score":0,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1461561524,"creation_date":1461561524,"body":"<blockquote>\n  <p>Does this mean that the interspecific hybrid is fertile?<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Yes<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>But is it possible, that an interspecific hybrid is fertile?<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>Yes<\/p>\n\n<p>You might be confused by the idea that by definition two species should not be able to interbreed. If so, then you should have a look at <a href=\"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/39664/how-could-humans-have-interbred-with-neanderthals-if-were-a-different-species/39669#39669\">How could humans have interbred with Neanderthals if we're a different species?<\/a>.<\/p>\n","answer_id":45573,"question_id":45058,"up_vote_count":0}],"link