 CNV region, but we don't know such region before.<\/p>\n\n<p>Paper: \"<a href=\"http://www.mdpi.com/2076-3905/4/3/339\" rel=\"nofollow\">Identification of Copy Number Aberrations in Breast Cancer\nSubtypes Using Persistence Topology<\/a>\".<\/p>\n","question_id":45433,"tags":["human-genetics","genomics"],"score":0,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":false,"view_count":32,"up_vote_count":0,"last_edit_date":1461219207},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/39c789e88085e17e3fdeef99b9fdea1e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":23306,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/23306/user23306","reputation":6,"display_name":"user23306"},"closed_date":1461219029,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/210cc4a4b2f281aaffe0b26521fe1ab8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1590,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1590/rg255","reputation":11513,"display_name":"rg255","accept_rate":66},"score":0,"post_id":45437,"edited":false,"creation_date":1461218950,"comment_id":79562,"body":"Your question was closed for a reason, deal with those problems and your original question might get reopened. Don&#39;t waste our time by just reposting your previous question."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/da1e8af33e12bfa60ea44b3af00c0d03?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"moderator","user_id":5144,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/5144/chris","reputation":31001,"display_name":"Chris"},"score":0,"post_id":45437,"edited":false,"creation_date":1461219023,"comment_id":79563,"body":"Please do <b>not<\/b> repost questions in a slightly modified form when the original question was closed as too broad, as this will happen again. Instead modify the original question and have it reopened."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/39c789e88085e17e3fdeef99b9fdea1e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":23306,"